build an HR database 

#1 retrieve the FIRST_NAME, LAST_NAME, EMPLOYEE_ID, and SALARY of employees whose manager's FIRST_NAME is 'Payam'.
#2 retrieve the FIRST_NAME, LAST_NAME, SALARY, DEPARTMENT_ID, and JOB_ID of employees whose JOB_ID matches the EMPLOYEE_ID 169. 
#3 retrieve the FIRST_NAME, LAST_NAME, and SALARY of employees whose salary is higher than the salary of an employee with the last name 'Ozer'
#4 retrieve distinct DEPARTMENT_ID, DEPARTMENT_NAME, MANAGER_ID, and LOCATION_ID from the DEPARTMENTS table
#5 query three actions using SQL variables and updates. First disables safe updates (SET SQL_SAFE_UPDATES = 0), then delete all employees from the department with the name 'Marketing', and enable safe updates. 
#6 calculate the average salary of all employees, retrieve the EMPLOYEE_ID, FIRST_NAME, LAST_NAME, and SALARY of employees whose salary is greater than or equal to the previously calculated average salary and whose first name or last name starts with 'J'.
